  "prompt": "Can you get pregnant without cervical mucus?",
  "response": "Cervical mucus plays an important role in fertility, as it helps facilitate the passage of sperm through the cervix and into the uterus. While it is possible to get pregnant without noticeable cervical mucus, it's typically more challenging. \n\nCervical mucus varies throughout the menstrual cycle, becoming more abundant and stretchy around ovulation, which helps sperm survive and swim toward the egg. However, some women may experience low levels of cervical mucus due to factors like hormonal imbalances, certain medications, or dehydration. In such cases, sperm can still travel through the cervical canal, and pregnancy can occur, but the chances may be reduced.\n\nIf you're trying to conceive and are concerned about cervical mucus or fertility, it might be helpful to consult with a healthcare provider for advice and potential solutions.",
